article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- — DaQuan Smith had 19 points in Radford's 73-56 win against VMI on Tuesday night. Smith shot 6 for 16 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 5 of 7 from the free throw line for the Highlanders (8-4). Chandler Turner scored 17 points while shooting 6 for 8, including 3 for 4 from beyond the arc, and added five rebounds. Kenyon Giles shot 5 for 13, including 2 for 6 from beyond the arc to finish with 13 points. The Keydets (2-9) were led by Tyran Cook, who posted 20 points. DJ Nussbaum added 14 points for VMI. Koree Cotton also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
